title: Did John F. Kennedy Proclaim Himself to Be a Jelly Doughnut?
subtitle: The notion that President John F. Kennedy referred to himself as a jelly doughnut in his famous 1963 speech in Berlin, Germany, is an old and false one.
author: David Mikkelson
vclaim: President John F. Kennedy called himself a jelly donut in his famous 1963 speech in Berlin, Germany.
